PRIVACY POLICY & TERMS OF SERVICE FOR PRIVAPOCKET
Effective Date: May 27, 2026

--- PART 1: PRIVACY POLICY ---

1. INTRODUCTION
Welcome to PrivaPocket (hereinafter referred to as the "App"). We are fully committed to protecting your personal financial privacy through a strict "offline-first" architectural design. By installing and using this App, you agree to the terms outlined in this document. 

2. LOG DATA AND ZERO-CLOUD ISOLATION
The App is explicitly engineered to function without external cloud infrastructure or servers. All personal financial records, wallet names, transaction logs, and balances are processed and stored exclusively within a secure local SQLite database on your physical device. We have zero technical means of accessing, reading, intercepting, or collecting your financial logs.

3. THIRD-PARTY SERVICES AND LIMITED ADVERTISING
To keep core features free, the App integrates Google AdMob to serve limited advertisements. 
- Rewarded Ads: Users may voluntarily watch a video advertisement in exchange for temporary access to premium features. 
- Data Collection by Third Parties: Google AdMob may use device identifiers (such as the Google Advertising ID) to serve relevant ads. The App itself does not pass any internal financial data to Google AdMob.
- Premium Ad Removal: Users who purchase the "Lifetime Pro Unlock" will have all advertisements removed permanently.

4. DEVICE PERMISSIONS USAGE
- Biometric Authentication: Used solely to gate access to the App interface locally. The App cannot read or store your biometric profiles.
- Local Storage / Camera Access: Used strictly if you choose to attach a photo of a physical receipt to a transaction.

5. DATA SAFETY COMPLIANCE
In alignment with Google Play mandates, we declare that no user data is collected by the developer, and no user data is shared with external third parties by the developer.

6. DATA DELETION
Because your data is entirely localized, you retain absolute control. Uninstalling the application or selecting "Clear Data" in your device settings will permanently wipe all local registries. This action cannot be undone.

